    h1 6 / 25 
      span.title — the treasure hunt
    p Today in class we did a treasure hunt, all over the city. We had to find lots of buildings and even some people—we walked for two hours! At the end, we couldn’t go any further, so we took a taxi back (it was John’s idea).  But we won the hunt! The prize: some cookies.
    p After, we all ate together at a small but cute restaurant—I forgot the name and where it is. My friend Christina (who took all of today’s pictures) and I went back to her house and studied for a bit. I had dinner at my house, and after, Christina and I went out to the central piazza!

